HEADWORD: Eftsoons
<hw>Eft*soons"</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>eftsone</ets>,
<ets>eftsones</ets>; AS. <ets>eft + s⟦omac⟧na</ets> soon. See
<er>Eft</er>, and <er>Soon</er>.]</ety> <def>Again; anew; a second time;
at once; speedily.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And, if he fall from his capel [horse] <qex>eftsone</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The champion stout <qex>eftsoons</qex> dismounted.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

